f":"https://vizhub.com","rel":["nofollow"]},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"https://vizhub.com"}]}]}],"toc":{"title":"","searchDepth":2,"depth":2,"links":[]}},"_type":"markdown","_id":"content:blog:test9.md","_source":"content","_file":"blog/test9.md","_extension":"md"},{"_path":"/blog/how-to-give-credit","_dir":"blog","_draft":false,"_partial":false,"_locale":"","title":"How To Give Credit","description":"","dek":"In which we do what is right by being clear about the contributions each member of the team brings to a project","inprogress":true,"date":"2023-09-03T18:18:33.000Z","modified":"2023-12-18T00:08:46.000Z","tags":"howto process","body":{"type":"root","children":[{"type":"element","tag":"h2","props":{"id":"how-to-give-credit"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"How To Give Credit"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"There was a maxim I once heard as a teenager and have valued ever since: "},{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"give credit, take blame"}]},{"type":"text","value":"."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Giving credit is an essential part of being a decent human. I see people fail at it surprisingly often."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Different fields have their own ways of doing it, and we can learn from these different approaches and try to taxonomize and find the tactics that best apply to our own situations."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In cinema, the focus is often on key roles the audience values like directors and lead actors. Academia has a nuanced system; the order of authors can indicate the level of contribution. Journalism uses bylines, putting the lead reporter's name first, and crediting photographers and graphics producers in captions next to their work, but almost never crediting Editors."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Looking across industry and history, let's find insights into how to properly acknowledge the work of others."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"If you care to look, your music streaming app doesn't just tell you the Artist who released the track; it tells you who's strumming the guitar, who's hitting the drums, and who's tweaking the soundboard. Streaming sites get a lot wrong when it comes to compensation, but in this one area, they are a model for an approach to proper credit, even if the media is distributed long after it was created, in ways the authors could have never predicted."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Journalism is another industry where stories are often the work of a team, at least one editor, a writer, maybe a photo editor and a graphics person. Yet, the byline at the top of the story often only features a single writer."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"What if each article credited the entire team? The editor who pruned the excess, the fact-checker who sifted fact from fiction, the intern who unearthed that crucial data point—all given their due."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Credit isn't a zero-sum game. Acknowledging the collective doesn't diminish the individual; it enriches the entire endeavor, both for the creator and whoever receives the work."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"why-giving-credit-is-important"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Why Giving Credit is Important"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In a world that often rushes to the finish line, the act of pausing to give credit might seem like a luxury. The skeptics might argue that giving credit muddies the waters, complicates the narrative, or even sparks legal quandaries. These people suck."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Let's be clear: the absence of acknowledgment isn't simplicity; it's wrong. It's a poisonous silence that can breed resentment, stifle innovation, and ultimately, erode entire teams."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The time it takes to attribute fairly is not a detour but an investment, one that pays dividends in trust and respect."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"how-to-give-credit-properly"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"How to Give Credit Properly"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Alright, you're convinced. You want to give your team credit for their work. But how do you do it properly, equitably, and consistently?"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h4","props":{"id":"verbal-acknowledgment"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Verbal Acknowledgment"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Be specific: value precision when describing each person's contributions, and actually pay attention to the parts of the project each person cared about deeply."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Timing: be upfront when giving credit, do it often, and in public."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Consistency: don't overlook quieter contributors, make sure to take the time to understand the contributions and speak honestly about each person"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Understand your team: some people prefer private thank-yous or different approaches"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Culture: encourage a culture of credit where everyone acknowledges each other's contributions as a habit"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"All forms: include all forms of contribution, from the person writing code to the person who washed dishes after that late-night working session"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h4","props":{"id":"written-acknowledgment"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Written Acknowledgment"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Document the Details: In reports, emails, or any official documents, be explicit about who contributed what. This ensures everyone's efforts are recognized and in the record."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Email Shoutouts: When communicating project updates, make it a point to name individuals and their specific contributions. It's a direct and effective way to show appreciation and highlight their achievements."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Social Media: Utilize social media and company platforms to publicly acknowledge team members. A LinkedIn mention or a spotlight in the company newsletter can significantly uplift morale and visibility."}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"the-impacts-of-giving-credit"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The Impacts of Giving Credit"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h4","props":{"id":"positive-impacts"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Positive Impacts"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Enhanced credibility"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Strengthened relationships; boosted morale and motivation"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Career advancement in academia and journalism"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h4","props":{"id":"negative-impacts-of-failing-to-give-credit"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Negative Impacts of Failing to Give Credit"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"ul","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Plagiarism and its consequences"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"li","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Strained professional relationships"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"case-studies"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Case Studies"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Rosalind Franklin and DNA Structure Discovery"}]},{"type":"text","value":": Rosalind Franklin's contribution to the discovery of the DNA double helix structure is a famous case of credit not being given where due. While James Watson, Francis Crick, and Maurice Wilkins received the Nobel Prize in 1962 for this discovery, Franklin's crucial contribution, particularly her X-ray diffraction images of DNA, was not adequately acknowledged during her lifetime."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Phil Knight and Nike’s Swoosh Logo"}]},{"type":"text","value":": The iconic Nike Swoosh was designed by Carolyn Davidson, a graphic design student, for a mere $35 in 1971. While Phil Knight and Nike gained massive recognition and profits, Davidson's contribution was relatively unknown until much later. Nike later acknowledged her role and compensated her with stock in the company."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The Matilda Effect in Scientific Research"}]},{"type":"text","value":": This term refers to the under-recognition of female scientists' contributions, named after the suffragist Matilda Joslyn Gage. A prominent example is the case of Chien-Shiung Wu, a physicist whose work was critical in the field of particle physics, but who did not receive the same level of recognition as her male counterparts."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"strong","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"James Somerton Youtube Controversy"}]},{"type":"text","value":": The saga of James Somerton is a recent and particularly egregious example of not giving credit. Somerton, known for his thought-provoking essays on LGBTQ+ representation in media, was found to be a serial plagiarist by HBomberguy, another YouTuber, who dissected his work in a comprehensive video titled \"Plagiarism and You (Tube).\" This wasn't a fleeting mention; nearly half of the four-hour video was dedicated to analyzing Somerton's content, highlighting dozens of instances of plagiarism where Somerton took a writer's work and modified it slightly before reciting it to a camera and soliciting Patreon supporters."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"conclusion"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Conclusion"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The notion that giving credit diminishes the role of the leader or disrupts industry norms is a relic of a bygone era—an era that didn't understand the synergistic magic of collective intelligence. True leadership is magnified, not minimized, by the act of extending credit where it's due. It's a gesture that says, \"I see you, I value you, and I recognize that my success is interwoven with your contributions.\""}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Credit and gratitude are a practice that transcends contractual obligations and enters the realm of ethical integrity. In a world full of competition and individual accolades, the act of giving credit becomes a revolutionary stance, a commitment to a culture of inclusivity, transparency, and mutual respect."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"p","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"In a world obsessed with individual achievement, giving credit is a radical act. It disrupts the narrative of the lone genius and recognizes the collective effort behind any meaningful endeavor. It's not just ethical; it's profoundly human. It's the way we say to each other, \"Your presence in this world makes a difference.\""}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h3","props":{"id":"additional-resources"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Additional Resources"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"h4","props":{"id":"industry-practices-in-credit"},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Industry Practices in Credit"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"table","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"thead","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"tr","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"th","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Industry"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"th","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Good Practices"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"th","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Bad Practices"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"th","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"What Can Be Learned"}]}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"tbody","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"tr","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Art"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Lists all contributors including the artist, muse, framer, etc."}]},{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Spotlight often solely on the artist"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Broad acknowledgment enriches the endeavor"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"tr","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Journalism"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Byline for lead reporter"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Often omits editors, fact-checkers, interns"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Layered credits could offer a fuller picture"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"tr","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Music"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Digital platforms list all roles: songwriter, producer, vocalist"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Issues with uncredited samples"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Transparency can be an art form"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"tr","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Software Development"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Open-source projects maintain a contributors list"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Contributions in proprietary code can be obscured"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Democratic, transparent crediting fosters collaboration"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"tr","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Visual Arts"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Artist biographies in exhibitions"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Art theft and plagiarism online"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Context adds depth to acknowledgment"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"tr","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Architecture"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Credits both the firm and lead architects"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Junior architects may go uncredited"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Balance between collective and individual acknowledgment"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"tr","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Sports"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Highlights key players and team effort"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Coaches and support staff may go unnoticed"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Collective effort is as important as individual performance"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"tr","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Publishing"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Detailed biographies of contributing authors"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Ghostwriting obscures actual contributors"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Transparency in crediting invisible labor"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"tr","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Fashion"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Lead designers share runway applause"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Fast fashion copies without credit"}]},{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Generous crediting avoids ethical pitfalls"}]}]},{"type":"element","tag":"tr","props":{},"children":[{"type":"element","tag":"td","props":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Video Games"}]},{"type":"element